(45, 89, 'Ophthalmology', '<h2>OPHTHALMOLOGY</h2><p>The Department of Ophthalmology of United Hospital provides both basic and specialized eye care services for patients. Our trained and experienced Consultant provides specialized treatment for a wide variety of eye problems.</p><p>Specialized equipment such as the argon laser for treatment of diabetic eye diseases, and computerized visual field analysers for assessment of glaucoma, are available. Our Consultant, trained in optometry, helps in the prescription of glasses for both adults and children. All surgeries are conducted at state-of-the-art operation theatres of the hospital, and over 90% of the surgeries do not require hospital admission. The theatre is equipped with a phaco-emulsification machine for small incision cataract surgery.</p>', '<h2>CONSULTATION &amp; APPOINTMENTS</h2><p>The department provides consultation services in level-4 through highly qualified and experienced Consultant, who carefully evaluates each patient. After diagnosing the patient’s condition, our Consultant discusses available treatment options and recommends the most effective treatment.</p>', '<h2>SERVICES AVAILABLE IN EYE CARE CENTRE :</h2><ul><li>Computerized Eye Test</li><li>Slit Lamp Eye Test</li><li>Tonometry</li><li>Glaucoma Screening</li><li>Contact Lens</li><li>Eyelid Surgery</li><li>Congenital Autograft</li><li>Cornea Transplantation</li><li>Squint Surgery</li><li>Glaucoma Surgery</li><li>DCR Surgery</li><li>Phaco Surgery</li></ul>', 'null', 'null', '202211140535ophthalmology.png', 0, 1, '2022-09-19 10:55:09', '2023-02-27 12:40:20'),
(46, 90, 'Orthopaedic', '<h2>ORTHOPAEDICS</h2><p>United Hospital Limited has one of best the orthopaedic department in the country, serving to provide 360º care as a Bone &amp; Joint Centre. The Department of Orthopaedics has two full-time Consultants, Two part-time Consultant, a number of junior doctors, and supporting paramedical staff trained to deliver a 100% success rate. Our team diagnoses, operates and treats problems affecting the bones, joints and muscles of patients encompassing all age groups.</p><p>The Department of Orthopaedics offers out-patient consultation services and procedures. It is well supported by fully equipped operation theatre (OT), intensive care units for pre- and post- operative care, as well as rehabilitation services in Physiotherapy Department. The state-of-the-art OT is equipped all updated facilities. The hospital is also equipped with CT scan (500 slice), MRI Scan (1.5 tesla), and Digital X-ray for prompt screening facilities.&nbsp;</p>', '<h2>CONDITIONS TREATED</h2><p>The orthopaedic conditions we commonly treat in our Department include:</p><ul><li>Arthritis</li><li>Back Pain</li><li>Bone and Soft Tissue Tumors</li><li>Broken bones</li><li>Concussions</li><li>Developmental Dysplasia of the Hip (DDH)</li><li>Dwarfism and Bone Dysplasias</li><li>FracturesBipolar Prosthesis</li><li>Hemiathroplasty by Austin Moore Prosthesis</li><li>Total Knee Replacement</li><li>Revision Surgery of Total Knee</li><li>Removal of Prosthetic implants</li><li>Lordosis</li><li>MCL Injuries</li><li>Osteochondritis Dissecans (OCD)</li><li>PCL Injuries</li><li>Scoliosis</li><li>Slipped Capital Femoral Epiphysis (SCFE)</li><li>Spinal Tumors</li><li>Spondylolysis</li><li>Spondylolisthesis</li><li>Sports Injuries</li><li>Tarsal Coalition</li><li>Torn ligaments</li><li>Torticollis</li></ul>', '<h2>REPAIR RECONSTRUCTION OF ALL BONE AND JOINT INJURIES CAUSED BY FALL OR TRAUMA AND TREATMENT OF CONGENITAL MUSCULO-SKELETAL DEFORMITIES.</h2><ul><li>Total Hip Replacement</li><li>Revision Surgery of Total Hip replacement</li><li>Hip Infections</li><li>Kyphosis</li><li>Hemiathroplasty by Bipolar Prosthesis</li><li>Hemiathroplasty by Austin Moore Prosthesis</li><li>Total Knee Replacement</li><li>Revision Surgery of Total Knee</li><li>Removal of Prosthetic implants</li><li>Lordosis</li><li>MCL Injuries</li><li>Osteochondritis Dissecans (OCD)</li><li>PCL Injuries</li><li>Scoliosis</li><li>Slipped Capital Femoral Epiphysis (SCFE)</li><li>Spinal Tumors</li><li>Spondylolysis</li><li>Spondylolisthesis</li><li>Sports Injuries</li><li>Tarsal Coalition</li><li>Torn ligaments</li><li>Torticollis</li></ul><p>Repair reconstruction of all bone and joint injuries caused by fall or trauma and&nbsp;Treatment of Congenital Musculo-skeletal deformities.</p>', 'null', 'null', '202211140535orthopedics.png', 0, 1, '2022-09-19 10:57:47', '2023-02-28 13:27:15');
