(86, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Rafiques  Salehin', '. MBBS, FCPS(BD), FRCS(Glasg), FRCS(Edin)', 'EID-19404', 'A-16765\r\n', 51, '2022100408461654051830_2_Prof. Dr. Rafiques Salehin.jpg', 1500, '<p>&middot;&nbsp;Obtained MBBS degree from Sher-E-Bangla medical college under Dhaka university in 1987, FCPS in Surgery from Bangladesh College of Physicians &amp; Surgeons (BCPS) in 1995, FACS in surgery from American college of surgeons, FRCS from Royal college of Surgeons of Edinburg, FRCS from Royal college of Surgeons of Glasgow in 1998.</p>\n\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;He worked in National Health Services (NHS) in UK for two years after FRCS.</p>\n\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;Worked in BIRDEM, Holy Family Hospital, Dhaka Medical college Hospital, Shaheed Suhrawardy Medical College during early life. Later worked as Resident Surgeon, Assist. Professor, Asso. Professor and Professor &amp; Head Department of Surgery in Sylhet MAG Osmani Medical college, Rajshahi Medical college, Dinajpur Medical College and Mugda Medical College. Before joining United Hospital he worked &nbsp;as Professor &amp; Head department of Surgery in Sir Salimullah Medical College &amp; Hospital, where he was also Head Department of Hepatobiliay &amp; Pancreatic Surgery.</p>\n\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;He is a regular examiner of under Graduate MBBS &amp; Post Graduate examination FCPS, MS.</p>\n\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;Received Training in different discipline of General, Endoscopic &amp; Laparoscopic Surgery in England, Singapore, Hongkong, Mumbai and Delhi.</p>\n\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;He has 32 year&rsquo;s experience of performing Huge Number of Major surgical cases, Cancer Surgeries. He is doing laparoscopic surgeries since 1995 &amp; is one of the Pioneer well reputed Advance Laparoscopic surgeon of the country.</p>\n\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;He has several Research works, publications &amp; presented several papers in national &amp; international scientific sessions.</p>\n\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;Demonstrated live workshop on Hepatobiliary Surgery in International session in 2021.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 15:46:24'),
