(117, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Mesbah Uddin Ahmed', 'MBBS, MS (ENT)', 'HS01352', 'A-11371\r\n', 38, '2022100406531476950843_2_dr mesbah.jpg', 1500, '<p>Prof. Dr. Mesbah Uddin Ahmed did his MBBS from Rangpur Medical College in 1982; after that he attained Post Graduation having MS in ENT in 2006 from Dhaka University.</p>\n\n<p>He has demonstrated expertise in managing all types of Ear, Nose &amp; Throat problems. He is skilled and experienced in varied types of ENT &amp; Head Neck Surgeries by endoscopic method and by using laser techniques. To name a few, these are removal of vocal cord polyp, papilloma and debulking of different forms of cancer; Pharyngeal surgery and voice restoration surgery, Endoscopic sinus &amp; Skull Base Surgery, Nasal Septal Surgery and Endoscopic DCR (Lacrimal Passage), Neck Surgery including thyroid surgery, Oral Cavity and Tongue surgery, Tonsillectomy and Adenoidectomy, Microsurgery of Ear and Hearing Restoration surgery.</p>\n\n<p>In his long career of over three decades in government job, he served in Sir Salimullah Medical College Hospital, Mitford, Dhaka Medical College &amp; Hospital, BSMMU, Shaheed Suhrawardy Medical College Hospital, Dhaka, Khulna Medical College Hospital among others.</p>\n\n<p>Since inception, he was serving in National Institute of ENT, Tejgaon, Dhaka and before joining United Hospital, he was serving there as Professor of ENT.</p>\n\n<p>Member:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Life member of Bangladesh Society of Otolaryngology&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Chief Editor of Bangladesh Journal of Otolaryngology</li>\n</ol>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 13:53:37'),
(118, NULL, 'Dr. Col. Anjuman Ara Beauty', 'MBBS, DCH, FCPS (Paed)', 'HS01405', 'A 18665\r\n', 92, '2022100406521485260364_2_IMG_1528.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 13:52:36'),
(119, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Md. Shamsul  Alam', 'MBBS, MCPS (Surgery), MS (Cardiothoracic Surgery)', 'HS01432', 'A-11367\r\n', 125, '2022100406481489467847_2_dr Shamsul Alam.jpg', 1500, '<p>Thoracic &amp; Esophageal Surgery</p><p>Professor &amp; Head of Dept. of Thoracic Surgery</p><p>National Institute of Diseases of Chest &amp; Hospital (NIDCH),&nbsp;Mohakhali, Dhaka.</p><p><br></p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Associations:</strong></p><p>Vice President&nbsp;&amp; Life Member, Bangladesh Association Thoracic Surgery (BATS)</p><p>Life Member, Society of Surgeons of Bangladesh (SOSB)</p><p>Life Member, Chest &amp; Heart Association of Bangladesh (CHAB)</p><p>Life Member, Teachers Association, NIDCH, Mohakhali, Dhaka</p><p>Life Member, Asthma Association, Bangladesh</p><p>Life Member, Bangladesh Medical Association (BMA)</p>', '<p>    MBBS, (Dhaka University), Sir Salimullah Medical College, Dhaka-1982</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;MCPS (Surgery), Bangladesh College of Physician &amp; Surgery (BCPS), 2000</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;MS, (Cardio vascular &amp; Thoracic Surgery), Dhaka University, 2002</p>', '<ol><li>Professor &amp; Head of Dept of Thoracic Surgery,&nbsp;National Institute of Diseases of Chest &amp; Hospital (NIDCH) Mohakhali, Dhaka</li><li>Worked as Thoracic Surgeon for 15 years posted as Registrar, Asst Prof.&nbsp;Associate Professor &amp; Professor of Thoracic Surgery at NIDCH, Dhaka and done numerous minor &amp; major Thoracic &amp;&nbsp;Esophageal surgery</li><li>Total experiences in Govt. service about 35 years.</li><li>Training in Video Assisted Thoracoscopic&nbsp;surgery (VATS) from Mumbai, India.</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-11-14 17:09:38'),
(120, NULL, 'Dr. Mostafa Aziz Sumon', 'MBBS, MCPS (Radiotherapy), MD (Radiation Oncology)', 'HS01463', '', 86, '2022100406501547703167_2_IMG_6510_edit.jpg', 1500, '<p><br></p>', '<ol><li>MBBS – Mymensingh Medical College, Under University of Dhaka- 2001</li><li>MD (Radiation Oncology)- 2012</li></ol><p><br></p>', '<ol><li>Head of Department, Department of Oncology, Kurmitola General Hospital, Dhaka</li><li>He is also the consultant of Oncology in Japan Bangladesh Friendship Hospital</li><li>He was awarded with “ABMF GOLD MEDAL” for best paper in 11th SAARC Federation of Oncology Cancer Congress 2016</li><li>He is trained in Bologna University, Italy and National University Hospital Singapore</li><li>He is an IAEA fellow and the Country coordinator of multinational, multicentre trial on “Evidence based on lab medicine in Oncological practice” under Yamaguchi University, Japan</li></ol><p><br></p>', 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-11-14 17:03:07'),
(121, NULL, 'Dr. Brig. Gen.Dr. S.M. Shameem  Waheed', 'MBBS, FCPS (Surgery), FCPS (Urology), Fellow SIU', 'HS01540', '', 132, '2022100406421593580419_2_Dr shameem.jpg', 1500, '<p><strong>Academic Record</strong></p>\n\n<p>Completed MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine and Surgery) in 1983-1988 from Sher-E-Bangla Medical College, Barishal, Bangladesh under the University of Dhaka</p>\n\n<p>Completed FCPS (Fellow of Bangladesh College of physicians and Surgeons) (Surgery) in 2002 from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons.</p>\n\n<p>Completed FCPS (Fellow of Bangladesh College of physicians and Surgeons) (Urology) in 2008 from Bangladesh college of physicians and Surgeons.</p>\n\n<p>Completed Fellow SIU (Societe International d Urologie) in 2010 from Muljibhai Patel Urology Hospital, Nadiad, Gujarat, India.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Work Experience</strong></p>\n\n<p>Worked as Trainee in General Surgery, Armed Forces Medical Institute, Dhaka Cantonment, Dhaka, Bangladesh, in 1994-1996</p>\n\n<p>Attached as Post-graduate trainee in Surgery, Bangladesh Sheikh Mujib Medical University, Dhaka, Bangladesh, in 2001-2002</p>\n\n<p>Trained in Urology at Combined Military Hospital, Dhaka &amp; Bangabandhu Sheikh Muzib Medical University, Dhaka, Bangladesh in 2006-2009.</p>\n\n<p>Trained as SIU Fellow in Urology, Muljibhai Patel Urology Hospital, Nadiad, Gujarat, India in2010.</p>\n\n<p>Observer Ship training in Urology, National University Hospital, Singapore in 2011</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 13:42:30'),
(122, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Taimor  Nawaz', 'MBBS (DMC), MRCP (UK)', 'HS01575', 'A-11443\r\n', 64, '2022100406411595074486_2_Dr. Taimor Nawaz.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Professor Taimor Nawaz is a highly qualified and trained physician specializing in Infectious Diseases &amp; Internal Medicine being the only US Board Certified clinician in the country in Infectious Diseases specialty</li>\n	<li>In 1992 and 1994, he passed American Board of Internal Medicine and Infectious Disease examination respectively and got certification</li>\n	<li>Prior to this, he received MRCP degree from the Royal College of Physicians of the United Kingdom in 1988</li>\n	<li>He also received Fellowship from London and Edinburgh&#39;s Royal College of Physicians and also from American College of Physicians</li>\n	<li>He was the International Advisor for Royal College of Physicians of London from 2000 to 2015</li>\n	<li>Before joining United Hospital, he was serving as Principal in Bangladesh Medical College from 2012 to 2017</li>\n	<li>Member of COVID steering committee of United Hospital</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 13:41:13'),
(123, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Shameem Anwarul Hoque\r\n', 'MBBS, FCPS (Otolaryngology)', 'HS01592', 'A-18030\r\n', 38, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(124, NULL, 'Dr. Reyan  Anis', 'MBBS (DMC), MRCP (UK)', 'HS01622', 'A-15647\r\n', 16, '2022100406241639479563_2_1527920169_2_dr reyan.jpg', 1500, '<p>Dr. Reyan Anis, MRCP, one of the most renowned cardiologists of the country has joined United Hospital of the capital, where she is now seeing patients full time and performing cardiac procedures at Cath Lab.</p>\n\n<p>After graduating from Dhaka Medical College in 1985, Dr. Anis worked for just over a year at CMH in Dhaka before moving abroad. She completed a program in Internal Medicine from Edinburgh Postgraduate Institute of Medicine in the United Kingdom in 1989 before joining Scotland&#39;s Royal Infirmary, Edinburgh as a clinical trainee where she worked until obtaining her MRCP in 1991.</p>\n\n<p>In 1992 she returned to Bangladesh to begin her clinical fellowship in Cardiology at NICVD and upon completion joined the Cardiology department of BIRDEM in the middle of 1994. From 1995 to 1997 Dr. Anis practiced at Kings College Hospital of London in United Kingdom before returning to BIRDEM to serve as Associate Professor of Cardiology. Dr. Anis remained at BIRDEM until 2001 when she joined the DAB Cardiac Center, where she played a crucial role in establishing their CCU and Cath lab facilities in 2002 and spent a year there as their Cardiology Consultant. Dr. Anis practiced at ZH Sikder Women&#39;s Medical College &amp; Hospital from 2003 to 2004 as a Senior Cardiology Consultant before joining Lab Aid Cardiac Hospital in 2004.</p>\n\n<p>In 2010, Dr. Reyan Anis was awarded a prestigious FRCP from the Royal College of Physicians, London.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to being nominated as United Nation&#39;s Examination Physician for Bangladesh, Dr. Anis has also published articles as a contributing author in numerous renowned cardiac journals and has participated in many prestigious seminars both at home and abroad.</p>\n\n<p>Before joining United Hospital, she served as Senior Consultant and Interventional Cardiologist at Lab Aid Cardiac Hospital for 14 years, establishing herself as one of the finest medical practitioners in the country.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>EDUCATION AND QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Fellow of the Royal College of Physicians of London, FRCP, 2010</li>\n	<li>Member of the Royal College of Physicians, MRCP (UK), 1991</li>\n	<li>Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery, MBBS, Dhaka Medical College, Dhaka University, Bangladesh, 1985.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Experiences</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Senior Consultant &amp; Interventional Cardiologist (Lab Aid Cardiac Hospital), Dhaka September 2004 to 31 May 2018</li>\n	<li>Senior Consultant Cardiologist (Z.H Sikder Woman&rsquo;s College and Hospital), Dhaka August 2003 till August 2004</li>\n	<li>Associate Professor / Consultant Cardiologist (DAB Cardiac Centre), June 2002 to July 2003</li>\n	<li>Associate Professor / Consultant Cardiologist (BIRDEM), Dhaka December 2001 to June 2002</li>\n	<li>Assistant Professor / Junior Consultant Cardiologist, BIRDEM, Dhaka August 1994 to November 2001</li>\n	<li>Clinical Fellowship, Cardiology NICVD, Dhaka February 1992 to February 1993</li>\n	<li>Medical Registrar, Royal Infirmary Edinburgh, Scotland, UK May to October 1991</li>\n	<li>Clinical Trainee, Royal Infirmary Edinburgh, Scotland, UK February to April 1991</li>\n	<li>Senior Medical Officer, Combined Military Hospital (CMH) June 1988 to December 1988</li>\n	<li>Junior Medical Officer, Combined Military Hospital (CMH) June 1988 to December 1988</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>CLINICAL EXPERIENCES</h2>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Dhaka Medical College Hospital (DMCH)</li>\n	<li>Combined Military Hospital (CMH)</li>\n	<li>Royal Infirmary Edinburgh (RIE)</li>\n	<li>National Institute of Cardiovascular Disease (NICVD)</li>\n	<li>BIRDEM</li>\n	<li>King College Hospital, London</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>SPECIALISATION/FIELD OF WORK</strong></p>\n\n<p>Interventional Cardiology</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 13:24:55'),
(125, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Mostaque Hassan', 'BDS, DDS, MCPS, FICCDE, FICD', 'HS01643', '372\r\n', 31, '2022100406231530503169_2_IMG_6519-1.jpg', 1500, '<p>Professor Dr Mostaque H Sattar is a renowned Creative Smile Designer and he knows the impact of a smile can have on someone’s life and self-confidence, brings his talents and experience with cosmetic dentistry from his early time of teaching and maintains a state-of-the-art practice. Dr. Sattar is specialty-trained in the full range of dentistry options specially implantology, orthodontics and cosmetic, and has helped create some of the most recognizable smiles in the world. Known throughout country as a dentist to the stars, he has the dental skills and artistic ability to give a movie-star smile too.</p><p>Rotarian Dr. Sattar is the Regent, ICD Section XV, region 41 Bangladesh, Vice president of national organization Bangladesh Dental Society and Bangladesh Orthodontic Society, Assistant Secretary, Asian Academy of Aesthetic Dentistry, President of South Asian Academy of Aesthetic Dentistry and other major dental organizations. He is now in Editorial Board of MICD Journal is a peer-reviewed online international journal and cosmetic dentistry: beauty &amp; science Published by Dental Tribune. He focuses on providing comprehensive minimal invasive or non-invasive dental care using safe techniques that have proven effective.</p><p><br></p><h2>CLINICAL EXPERIENCES</h2><ol><li>Family Dentistry Banani, House 4, Road 4, Block F Banani, Dhaka, Bangladesh</li><li>Family Dentistry Dhanmondi 13/1, 2nd Floor, Fatema Arcade, Road No-5, Dhaka 1205</li><li>Family Dentistry Chittagong h- 159, Plot-20, Road-11. K.B. Fazlul Kader Road, Panchlaish, Chittagong - 4203</li></ol><p><strong>INTERNATIONAL AND REGIONAL CONFERENCE PRESENTATIONS</strong></p><p>1. Invited Speaker on Smile Design: Beauty_ art and Science 15 May 2018 at Health Science University of Hokkaido, Japan</p><p>2. Invited Keynote Speaker on Smile Design: Beauty_ art and Science workshop at 31st International Conference on Dentistry &amp; Oral Care held on May 18-19, 2018 at Hyatt Regency Osaka, Japan.</p><p>3. Invited Speaker at CSM Implant conference hotel Piccadilly, Delhi, India 22 April 2018</p><p>4. Invited Speaker on Oral Implantology &amp; Tissue Regeneration ACOITR conference 16-18 March, 2018 Kathmundu Nepal</p><p>5. Course Director: Intermediate Course on Dental Implant, Osstem Center, Dhaka, Bangladesh,</p><p>6. Moderator, 4th Thai-German International Congress, 10-12 January, 2018 Chiang Mai, Thailand</p><p>7. Invited Keynote Speaker on Smile Design: Beauty_ art and Science at APDC 2017 Dental and Oral Health Conference 10-12 July 2017 Kualalumpur, Malaysia</p><p>8. Invited Keynote Speaker on Smile Design: Beauty_ art and Science 1st Inaugural International Induction Ceremony and Scientific Conference, ICD Section XV 07-08 Oct 2017, UITM, Kualalumpur, Malaysia</p><p>9. Invited ICD speaker Mandalay dental Conference Myanmar 21-23 July 2017</p><p>10. Invited Keynote Speaker on Beauty_ art and Science of Smile Design at XI Annual Conference, Indian Dental Association Kolkata Branch, 4-5 Nov 2017, Kolkata, India.</p><p>11. Invited Speaker on Smile Design: Beauty_ art and Science at International Dental Congress Nepal&nbsp;11-12 November 2017 Hotel Hyatt Regency, Kathmandu, Nepal</p><p>12. Invited Keynote Speaker on Smile Design: Beauty_ art N Science 2016 at Southwestern University Phinma, Cibu Philippine.</p><p>13. APDC 2016 Hong Kong Asia Pacific dental Conference 17-19 July P R China.</p><p>14. FDI 2013 Istanbul. Annual World Dental Congress. 28-31 August 2013 – Istanbul, Turkey.</p><p>15. 66th Indian Dental Conference 22-25 Feb 2013, Science City, Kolkata, India</p><p>16. Dentistry Vision 2010 of Dental Practitioners Forum of India New Delhi, India</p><p>17. The South Asian Cosmetic &amp; Aesthetic Dental Regional Congress-2011 Colombo, Srilanka</p><p>18. 2nd South Asian Academy of Aesthetic Dentistry Conference 2011, Bangalore, India</p><p>19. Bangladesh Academy of Aesthetic and cosmetic dentistry Conference 2010 Dhaka, Bangladesh</p><p>20. The 1st South Asian Cosmetic &amp; Aesthetic Dental Congress-2009, Kathmandu, Nepal</p><p>21. Numerous local presentations</p><p><strong>AWARDS, FELLOWSHIPS, GRANTS</strong></p><p>1. Glaxo Smithkline GSK Bangladesh award of BD Tk.100,000.00 (Taka One Hundred Thousand only) to publish a Book Chair Side FAQ, Dental and Oral Health Education Book, 1st Edn. 2006 ISBN 984-32-3322-0</p><p>2. Honorary Fellowship of South Asian Academy of Aesthetic dentistry 2011, Bangalore, India</p><p>3. Fellowship of International College of Dentist FICD 2013</p><p>4. Fellowship of International College of Continuing Dental Education FICCDE 2013</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Membership and Position:</strong></p><p>1. Vice President, Bangladesh Dental Society (National organization)</p><p>2. Vice President, Bangladesh Orthodontic Society</p><p>3. Assistant Secretary, Asian Academy of Aesthetic Dentistry</p><p>4. President, South Asian Academy of Aesthetic Dentistry</p><p>5. Regent, International College of Dentist, section xv, reg</p>', '<ol><li>BDS Bachelor of Dental Surgery – Dhaka Dental College under University of Dhaka - 1983</li><li>DDS Diploma in Dental Surgery – IPGMR under University of Dhaka, 1989-90</li><li>MCPS – Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons, Mohakhali, Dhaka-Bangladesh – 1990</li><li>Honorary fellowship: FSAAAD, FICD and FICCDE</li></ol><p><br></p>', '<ol><li>Professor and Principal, City Dental College &amp; Hospital, 73/A, Nikunjo 2 (North), Beside Hotel Le-Meridian, Airport road Dhaka-1229 Bangladesh February 2016- till today.</li><li>Associate Professor and Head, Department of Dentistry, Jessore medical College and Hospital July 2013 to Feb 2016</li><li>Associate Professor, Orthodontic, Dhaka Dental College &amp; Hospital,&nbsp;June 2010 to July 2013</li><li>Associate Professor / Assistant Professor, Head, Dental Unit, Chittagong Medical College &amp; Hospital, November 2000 to June 2010</li><li>Assistant Professor and Head, Dental Unit, Sir Salimullah Medical College &amp; Mitford Hospital, July 1999 to November 2000</li><li>Assistant Professor, Orthodontics, Orthodontic, Dhaka Dental College &amp; Hospital, July 1995 to June 1999</li><li>Lecturer, Orthodontics, Orthodontic, Dhaka Dental College &amp; Hospital, July 1988 to June 1995&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ol><p><br></p>', 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-11-14 16:58:25'),
(126, NULL, 'Dr. Prashanta Prasun Dey', 'MBBS, MD (Endocrinology)', 'HS01724', 'A-16045\r\n', 36, '2022100406211580642874_2_dr prasun.jpg', 1500, '<p>He passed MBBS in 1986 from Mymensingh Medical College. He has done his MD in Endocrinology &amp; Metabolism on 2006 from BIRDEM. Before joining as Consultant Diabetology &amp; Endocrinology at United Hospital, he has had working &amp; teaching experience at Khawaja Yunus Ali Medical College Hospital, Sirajganj and Kumudini Womens Medical College Hospital in Tangail</p><p><br></p>', '<ol><li>MBBS – Mymensingh Medical College - 1986</li><li>MD (Endocrinology &amp; Metabolism)– BIRDEM – 2006</li></ol><p><br></p>', '<ol><li>Associate professor in the Kumudini Women’s Medical College, Mirzapur, Tangail from 2012 till date</li><li>Associate professor of Department of Endocrinology &amp; Metabolism in the Khawaja Yunus Ali Medical College Hospital, Sirajganj from 2007 to 2012</li></ol><p><br></p>', 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-11-14 16:57:07'),
(127, NULL, 'Dr. Nasrin  Hossain', 'MBBS, FCPS (Obstetrics and Gynaecology), FCPS (Gynaecological Oncology)', 'HS01725', 'A-29217\r\n', 85, '2022100406211544633219_2_dr nasrin.jpg', 1500, '<p>She passed MBBS in 1998 from Sylhet M.A.G Osmani Medical College. She has done her FCPS in Obstetrics and Gynaecology on 2010 from College of Physicians and Surgeons of Bangladesh. Thereafter she completed FCPS in Gynaecological Oncology in 2018 from College of Physicians and Surgeons of Bangladesh. She had been completed specialized Fellowship Training on Gynaeoncology from Tata Memorial Hospital, Mumbai, India in 2016. Before joining as Consultant Obstetrics and Gynaecology at United Hospital, she has had working experience at National Institute of Cancer Research &amp; Hospital (NICRH), Mymensingh Medical College Hospital and Shaheed Suhrawardy Medical College and Hospital, Dhaka.</p><p><br></p>', '<ol><li>MBBS – Sylhet M.A.G Osmani Medical College - 1998</li><li>FCPS (Obstetrics and Gynaecology) – College of Physicians and Surgeons of Bangladesh – 2010</li><li>FCPS (Gynaecological Oncology)- College of Physicians and Surgeons of Bangladesh – 2018</li></ol><p><br></p>', '<ol><li>Asst. Professor&nbsp;of Gynaecological Oncology in the National Institute of Cancer Research &amp; Hospital (NICRH), Mohakhali, Dhaka from 2013 till now</li><li>Junior Consultant, Obstetrics and Gynecology in&nbsp;Mymensingh Medical College Hospital from 2011 to 2013</li><li>Indoor Medical Officer, Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology in the Shaheed Suhrawardy Medical College and Hospital, Dhaka from 2006 to 2008</li></ol><p><br></p>', 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-11-14 16:56:16'),
(128, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Hazera  Khatun', 'MBBS, MCPS (Obstetrics and Gynaecology), MS (Obstetrics and Gynaecology)', 'HS01741', 'A-13796\r\n', 85, '2022100406171547353344_2_IMG_1119-Edit.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained her MBBS degree from&nbsp; Rangpur Medical College in 1983</li>\n	<li>Completed MCPS on Obstetrics and Gynaecology in 1991 from BCPS (Bangladesh College of Physician &amp; Surgery); and later successfully accomplished MS in Obstetrics and Gynaecology in 2005</li>\n	<li>She worked as an Assistant Professor in the Obstetrics and Gynaecology department in Dhaka Medical College for 5 years</li>\n	<li>Later joined in Shaheed Suhrawardy Medical College and Hospital, Dhaka and served there as an Associate Professor for 3 years, thereafter as a Professor in the same institute for 2 years</li>\n	<li>Internationally trained to handle complicated Obstetrics and Gynaecology surgery (including laparoscopic surgeries), Gynae-onco surgery, Infertility and also an expert in managing high risk pregnancy</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 13:17:36'),
(129, NULL, 'Dr. Amit  Wazib', 'MBBS, FCPS (Medicine), MD (Neurology)', 'HS01763', 'A-37004\r\n', 79, '2022100406161550409263_2_IMG_2889.jpg', 1500, '<p>He passed MBBS in 2003 from Dhaka Medical College. He has done his FCPS in Medicine on 2009 from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons. Thereafter, he completed his MD on Neurology from Dhaka Medical College in 2013. Before joining as Consultant Neurology at United Hospital, he has had working experience at Dhaka Medical College, Dhaka Community Medical College &amp; Shahabuddin Medical College.</p>', '<p><br></p><ol><li>MBBS – Dhaka Medical College - 2003</li><li>FCPS (Medicine) – Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons – 2009</li><li>MD (Neurology) – Dhaka Medical College – 2013</li></ol>', '<p><br></p><ol><li>Associate Professor &amp; Head of the Department of Neurology in Shahabuddin Medical College &amp; Hospital from 2017 till now</li><li>Assistant Professor of Medicine Department of Dhaka Community Medical College in 2017</li><li>Junior Consultant, Department of Neurology &amp; Medicine in Dhaka Medical College Hospital from 2013 to 2017</li></ol>', 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-11-14 16:40:18'),
