(19, NULL, 'Dr. Mohammad Abdur Rahman', 'MBBS, DCH (Child Health), MCPS (Paediatrics), FCPS (Paediatrics)', 'EID-12306', 'A-35056', 77, '2022100410191579677438_2_IMG_6368.jpg', 1500, '<p>He passed MBBS in 2002 from Sher-E-Bangla Medical College, Barisal under the University of Dhaka. He has done MCPS (Paediatrics) in 2016 and FCPS (Paediatrics) in 2019 from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons (BCPS), Dhaka. He completed Diploma in Child Health (DCH) from Dhaka Shishu Hospital in 2008. He worked in Central Hospital Dhaka from 2006 to 2010. He joined United Hospital in 2010 as a specialist of Paediatrics &amp; Neonatology department and serving as Junior Consultant from 2017.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:19:43'),
(20, NULL, 'Dr. Md. Iqbal Hossain', 'MBBS, MRCP (Ireland)', 'EID-12321', 'A-15506', 64, '2022100410161628341235_2_1475498626_2_dr iqbal.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS degree from Dhaka Medical College under University of Dhaka in 1985</li>\n	<li>Completed MRCP in Internal Medicine in 2003 from Royal College of Physicians, Ireland</li>\n	<li>Received training in different disciplines of Epidemiology of Rheumatic Fever and Rheumatic heart disease from Aichi Medical University, Japan in 1991</li>\n	<li>Worked in different hospital of abroad such as Ipoh General Hospital and Queen Elizabeth Hospital of Malaysia, National University Hospital and Tan Tock Seng Hospital of Singapore from 2000 to 2007</li>\n	<li>Worked in National University of Singapore (NUS) as Research Coordinator from 2007 to 2010</li>\n	<li>Joined United Hospital in 2010 and serving as Consultant in Internal Medicine</li>\n	<li>Member of COVID steering committee of United Hospital</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:16:31'),
(21, NULL, 'Dr. Nighat  Ara', 'MBBS, MCPS', 'EID-12346', 'A-30069', 85, '2022100410151639460387_2_1623230521_2_Dr. Nighat IMG_4760.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:15:44'),
(22, NULL, 'Dr. Md. Rashid Un Nabi', 'MBBS, M.phill (Radiotherapy) IAEA Fellow (Thailand), VARIAN Fellow (India) KFDA Fellow (Korea), UICC Fellow (Singapore)', 'EID-12382', 'A-19160', 86, '2022100410131628341031_2_1473245950_2_dr Nabi.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS degree from Chittagong Medical College under Chittagong University in 1989</li>\n	<li>Completed Masters of Philosophy (M.Phil) in Radiotherapy from Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University (BSMMU) in 1998</li>\n	<li>Received fellowship training in Radiation Oncology from Chulalongkorn Hospital, Bangkok, Thailand, Tata Memorial Hospital, Mumbai, India, National University Hospital, Seoul, South Korea and National Cancer Centre, Singapore</li>\n	<li>Worked in National Institute of Cancer Research &amp; Hospital as Assistant Professor in the department of Radiation Oncology from 2003 to 2009</li>\n	<li>Joined at United Hospital as Consultant in the department of Radiation Oncology in 2010</li>\n	<li>Pioneer in radiotherapy endeavors of the country under his leadership have been carried out in United Hospital Cancer Care Centre like providing radiation to patients as young as 4 years and as old as 94 years, specialization in Respiratory Gated Cardiac Sparing Radiation to breast cancer patients, DIBH (deep inspiration breath holding) based SBRT to lung, liver, SRT/ SRS to Brain tumour patient etc</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:13:39'),
(23, NULL, 'Dr. Afsari  Ahmad', 'MBBS, FCPS', 'EID-12716', 'A29982', 85, '2022100410121576130985_2_Dr Afsari Ahmed2.jpg', 1500, '<p>She passed MBBS in 1999 from Sher-E-Bangla Medical College Barisal under University of Dhaka. She did her FCPS in Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology from Bangladesh College of Physicians &amp; Surgeons (BCPS) in 2009. She also had training in different discipline of Breast feeding, GDM and Colposcopy. She worked in International Medical College, Gazipur as Assistant Professor from 2009 to 2011. &nbsp;Thereafter she worked in United Hospital as specialist from 2011 and in from 2019 she worked as Associate Consultant in the department of Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:12:46'),
(24, NULL, 'Dr. Syeda Fahmida Hossain', 'MBBS, FCPS', 'EID-12800', 'A-40893', 64, '2022100410091576066805_2_dr fahmida(1).jpg', 1500, '<h3>She passed MBBS in 2004 from Dhaka Medical College &amp; Hospital under University of Dhaka. She did her FCPS in Internal Medicine from Bangladesh College of Physicians &amp; Surgeons (BCPS) in 2011. She worked in National Heart Foundation &amp; Square Hospital as a Medical Officer from 2006 to 2007. Thereafter she joined in Dhaka Medical College &amp; hospital from 2008 to 2011. After that she joined in United Hospital as a Specialist from 2011 and in 2016 worked as a Junior Consultant at United Hospital Ltd.</h3>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:09:45'),
(25, NULL, 'Prof. Brig Gen Zahid Mahmud (Retd)', 'FCPS(Haematology)', 'EID-12829', '8608', 54, '2022100410101627901858_2_1452433996_2_Brig-Gen-(Retd)-Prof.-Zahid-Mahmud.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:10:17'),
(26, NULL, 'Dr. Ashim Kumar Sengupta', 'MBBS, M.Phil', 'EID-13037', 'A 29369', 86, '2022100410061582092990_2_Ashim Kumar Sengupta_IMG_5980_for Website_1.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS degree from&nbsp; Sylhet M A G Osmani Medical College &amp; Hospital in 1998</li>\n	<li>Completed his&nbsp; Post-graduate training in Internal Medicine in 1999</li>\n	<li>In 2003 he completed his M Phil in Radiotherapy from Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University, Dhaka</li>\n	<li>He worked as a trainee in Clinical Oncology (Medical Oncology, Radiation Oncology, Pain and Palliative Care Medicine) at AMRI Hospitals, Kolkata from 2005 to 2006 under close supervision of Dr. Prasenjit Chatterjee, a renowned Consultant Clinical Oncologist</li>\n	<li>Later, he received training in Medical and Radiation Oncology from National Cancer Center (NCC), Singapore in 2011</li>\n	<li>He worked as an Assistant Professor of Oncology in Khwaja Yunus Ali Medical College &amp; Hospital of Sirajgonj from 2007 to 2012</li>\n	<li>He is serving in United Hospital Cancer Care Centre providing Clinical and Radiation Oncology consultation and guidelines and since 2012 till mid 2020 he has managed more than Seven Thousand Cancer cases under his supervision</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:06:30'),
(27, NULL, 'Dr. Mohammad Moshiur Rahman', 'MBBS, FCPS, DCH (Dublin), MRCP (Dublin)', 'EID-13070', '7368', 92, '2022100410051476111946_2_dr moshiur rahman.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS degree from Dhaka Medical College under University of Dhaka in 1978</li>\n	<li>Completed Diploma in Child Health (DCH) from National University of Ireland in 1994</li>\n	<li>Completed FCPS from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons (BCPS) in 2007</li>\n	<li>Achieved MRCP from Royal College of Physicians of Ireland in 2009</li>\n	<li>Worked as Assistant Professor in the department of Paediatrics &amp; Neonatology in Jahurul Islam Medical College &amp; Hospital from 1994 to 2000</li>\n	<li>After that worked in the department of Paediatrics &amp; Neonatology in King Khaled General Hospital, Saudi Arabia from 2000 to 2005</li>\n	<li>Joined and worked in Royal Hospital for Sick Children, Glasgow, UK as MRCP (Paediatrics &amp; Neonatology) trainee from 2005 to 2006</li>\n	<li>Thereafter he served in Maternity &amp; Children Hospital, Sakaka, Saudi Arabia from 2008 till 2012 as Specialist Physician and Paediatric ICU Coordinator in the department of Paediatrics &amp; Neonatology</li>\n	<li>Serving United Hospital as a Consultant in the department of Paediatrics &amp; Neonatology since 2012</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:05:48'),
(28, NULL, 'Dr. Md. Mahbub Alam\n', '', 'EID-13202', '6653', 47, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(29, NULL, 'Dr. Runa  Laila', 'MBBS, FCPS', 'EID-13417', 'A-42108', 92, '2022100410031576067442_2_Dr Runa.jpg', 1500, '<h3>She passed MBBS in 2004 from Sher-E-Bangla Medical College Under the University of Dhaka.She did her FCPS in Paediatrics from Bangladesh College of Physician and Surgeons (BCPS) in 2013. She also had training in different discipline of Paediatrics in Dhaka Medical College &amp; BSMMU.&nbsp; She worked in Neonatal &amp; Paediatric General Hospital, Dhanmondi from 2007 to 2008. Thereafter she worked in Northern International Medical College &amp; hospital in 2013.She joined in United Hospital as a Junior Consultant from 2013 till now.&nbsp;</h3>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:03:47'),
(30, NULL, 'Dr. Mohammad Jahangir Talukder', 'MBBS, MRCP (UK.)', 'EID-13426', 'A 7322', 64, '2022100410011471435052_2_Dr Jahangir Talukder.jpg', 1500, '<p>Obtained M.B.B.S from MAG Osmani Medical College, Sylhet; under Chittagong University in 1978. Completed internship in Sir Salimullah Medical College. Worked for seven years under Ministry of Health, Bangladesh.</p>\n\n<p>Joined Ministry of Health Saudi Arabia in 1986. Worked in different institutions till 2001. Transferred to Al Rass General Hospital in December 2001 and worked as Medical Resident Officer till 2008. During this 8 years, obtained extensive training in the management of critical patient in different field of medicine like Neurology, Cardiology, Infectious disease, Pulmonology, Nephrology, Rheumatology, Toxicology, A&amp;E and Intensive Care. Obtained ACLS and BLS certificate. Obtained MRCP (UK) in May, 2008 and joined as Medical Specialist in the same hospital. Worked there till July,2012.</p>\n\n<p>On July, 2012 joined as Chief of the Department of Medicine at Al-Nabhaniya General Hospital.</p>\n\n<p>Joined United Hospital Ltd, as Associate Consultant, Medicine, from on 15 August, 2013 to till now.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:01:56'),
(31, NULL, 'Dr. Polly  Ahmed', 'MBBS, FCPS', 'EID-13635\r\n', 'A-38347\r\n', 85, '2022100410011576068107_2_Dr Polly Ahmed.jpg', 1500, '<p>She passed MBBS in 2003 from Sir Salimullah Medical College under University of Dhaka. She did her FCPS in Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology from Bangladesh College of Physicians &amp; Surgeons (BCPS) in 2013. She also had training in different discipline of Laparoscopy and Hysteroscopy. She worked in Holy Family Red Crescent Medical College &amp; Hospital from 2004 to 2006. Thereafter she worked in BIRDEM Hospital from 2006 to 2007. She Joined in United Hospital as a Junior Consultant in the department of Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology from 2011 till now.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>OPD TIMING: 06:00 PM To 09:00 PM, DAYS: SATURDAY &amp;&nbsp;MONDAY</strong></p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 17:01:14'),
(32, NULL, 'Dr. Sharif  Ahmed', 'MBBS, M.Phil (Radiotherapy)', 'EID-13695\r\n', 'A-41561\r\n', 86, '2022100409581587555388_2_Dr Sharif.jpg', 1500, '<p>He passed MBBS in 2004 from Sir Salimullah Medical College under University of Dhaka. He did his M.Phil in Radiotherapy from Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University in 2012. He also had training in different discipline of Radiation Oncology in Singapore &amp; India. He worked in National Healthcare Network as Medical Officer. Thereafter he joined in Cancer Foundation Hospital, Lalmatia. He joined at United Hospital as specialist in Oncology department in 2014 and in the same institution he is working as a Junior Consultant from 2018 till now.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:58:45'),
(33, NULL, 'Dr. Md. Rakib Hossain\r\n', 'MBBS, DLO, MCPS (ENT)', 'EID-13724\r\n', 'A-38976\r\n', 38, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(34, NULL, 'Dr. S. M. Zakir Khaled', 'MBBS, MS(CTS)', 'EID-14136\r\n', 'A-31925\r\n', 15, '2022100409551576147303_2_Dr. S M Zakir Khaled.jpg', 1500, '<p>He passed MBBS in 2000 from University of Science &amp; Technology, Chittagong (USTC) under the University of Chittagong. He did his MS in Cardio-thoracic Surgery from National Heart Foundation under University of Dhaka in 2014. He worked in National Heart Foundation as Surgical Resident from 2005 to 2014. Thereafter he worked in Square Hospital as a Specialist in Cardiac Surgery department from 2014 to 2015. After that he joined United Hospital in 2015 and now serving as a Junior Consultant in Cardiac Surgery department.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>OPD TIMING: 06:00 PM To 09:00 PM,&nbsp;DAYS: SUNDAY &amp;&nbsp;TUESDA</strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:55:10'),
(35, NULL, 'Dr. Afreed Jahan', 'MBBS, MD, PH.D', 'EID-14233\r\n', 'A-42289\r\n', 16, '2022100409521639460553_2_1623228498_2_Dr. Afreed IMG_4820.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:52:57'),
(36, NULL, 'Dr. Tania Mahbub', 'MBBS, MD (Nephrology)', 'EID-14247\r\n', 'A-37115\r\n', 78, '2022100409531539505950_2_Tania Mahbub.jpg', 1500, '<p>Dr. Tania Mahbub graduated (MBBS) from Sher-e-Bangla Medical College, Barisal under the University of Dhaka in 2001. She joined in Government job in 2005 and served in renowned Government tertiary care hospitals, notably in Dhaka Medical College Hospital, Sir Salimullah Medical College (Mitford) Hospital and Kurmitola General Hospital. She completed her four years of fellowship training in Medicine under BCPS and completed Doctor of Medicine (MD) in Nephrology from Dhaka Medical College in 2012.</p>\n\n<p>In 2013, Dr. Tania attended the Multi Organ Transplant Centre at Royal Victoria Hospital under the auspices of McGill University Heath Centre (MUHC), Montreal, Canada for pursuing a prestigious International Fellowship in Nephrology duly awarded by the International Society of Nephrology (ISN). She won this highly competitive position by virtue of her extraordinary merit and practical exposition. This esteemed fellowship rendered her an opportunity to undertake rigorous training there for one year in Cadaveric and Living Donor Transplantation as well as in Critical Care Nephrology. Having completed this fellowship training successfully, she became the first female Renal Transplant Fellow in Bangladesh being trained abroad. Dr. Tania has an accolade of research work which have been published in numerous scientific journal in home and abroad. She has special interest in Glomerular disease, critical case Nephro dialysis. She joined United Hospital Ltd in 2015 and currently is serving here as Consultant, Nephrology.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:53:43'),
(37, NULL, 'Dr. Tanveer Bin Latif', 'MBBS, MRCP (UK),Specialty Certified in Nephrology (UK)', 'EID-14396\r\n', 'A-32346\r\n', 78, '2022100409511475998131_2_dr tanvir latif.jpg', 1500, '<p><strong>Experienced and adept in managing Haemodialysis Centre with special interest&nbsp; in Kidney Glomerular Disorder&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Dr. Tanveer Bin Latif,&nbsp; completed his MBBS from Dhaka Medical College in 2000. After that he obtained his MRCP (UK) from The Royal College of Physicians of the United Kingdom in 2008</li>\n	<li>He completed his Fellowship in Nephrology from the National University Hospital (NUH), Singapore with emphasis on Critical Care Nephrology and Renal Transplantation in 2011</li>\n	<li>Completed the Specialty Certificate Examination in&nbsp; Nephrology (UK) in 2018 conducted by The Renal Association (UK) and The Federation of Royal Colleges of the United Kingdom</li>\n	<li>He has worked in renowned institutions in the country like BIRDEM and also abroad in Middlesex Hospital, London, UK</li>\n	<li>He has special interest in Kidney Glomerular Disorder and has performed close to 150 Renal Biopsy procedures so far. He has participated in many international seminars on Kidney Disease and Diabetes</li>\n	<li>Before joining as Consultant in United Hospital, he was serving as Associate Professor and Head of the Department of Nephrology at Uttara Adhunik Medical College</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:51:31'),
(38, NULL, 'Dr. Sonjoy Biswas', 'MBBS,MS (CTS),FCPS (CVS)', 'EID-14407\r\n', 'A-34114\r\n', 15, '2022100409501576147101_2_Dr. Sanjoy Biswas.jpg', 1500, '<p>He passed MBBS in 2001 from Sir Salimullah Medical College under University of Dhaka. He did his MS in Cardio-thoracic Surgery (CTS) from National Heart Foundation Hospital &amp; Research Institute (NHFC &amp; RI) in 2013. He completed his FCPS in CVS from Bangladesh College of Physicians &amp; Surgeons (BCPS) in 2015. He also completed Fellow from Harefield Hospital, London, United Kingdom in 2013. He worked in National Heart Foundation Hospital &amp; Research Institute (NHFC &amp; RI) as Surgical Resident from 2013 to 2014 and as Register in the same institute from 2014 to 2015. Thereafter he joined in United Hospital as a Cardiac Surgery specialist in 2015 and in the same institution he is working as a Junior Consultant in the department of Cardiac Surgery from 2019 till now.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>OPD TIMING: 06:00 PM To 09:00 PM, DAYS:&nbsp;MONDAY&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;WEDNESDAY</strong></p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:50:59'),
(39, NULL, 'Dr. Tunaggina Afrin Khan', 'MBBS, MD', 'EID-14430\r\n', 'A-43196\r\n', 16, '2022100409491576146001_2_IMG_5576_Tunagina-1.jpg', 1500, '<p>She passed MBBS in 2005 from Sir Salimullah Medical College, Dhaka under University of Dhaka. She did his MD in Cardiology from Dhaka Medical College in 2014. She worked in Ibrahim Cardiac Hospital &amp; Research Institute as Resident, Cardiology from 2008 to 2011. Before joining at United Hospital she worked in Anwar Khan Modern Medical College as Assistant Professor in Cardiology department from 2014 to 2015.</p>\n\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>OPD TIMING: 06:00 PM To 09:00 PM,&nbsp;DAYS: SATURDAY, SUNDAY &amp;&nbsp;MONDAY</strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:49:45'),
(40, NULL, 'Dr. Md. Shakhawat  Hossain', 'MBBS, MS (CTS)', 'EID-14450\r\n', 'A-44290\r\n', 15, '2022100409491576147584_2_Dr Md Shakhawat Hossain.jpg', 1500, '<p>He passed MBBS in 2005 from Mymensingh Medical College under the University of Dhaka. He did his MS in Cardio-thoracic Surgery (CTS) from National Heart Foundation under University of Dhaka in 2015. He also had Vascular training from National Institute of Cardio Vascular Disease. He worked in National Heart Foundation as Senior Medical Officer from 2007 to 2016. Thereafter he joined United Hospital&nbsp;in Cardiac Surgery Department in&nbsp;2016.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>OPD TIMING: 06:00 PM To 09:00 PM,&nbsp;DAYS: SUNDAY &amp;&nbsp;TUESDAY</strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:49:15'),
(41, NULL, 'Dr. Mohammad Nadim Bin\r\n', '', 'EID-14455\r\n', 'A-57708\r\n', 35, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(42, NULL, 'Dr. Zeenat  Sultana', 'MBBS, FCPS', 'EID-14526\r\n', 'A-40945\r\n', 64, '2022100409471576067154_2_Dr Zeenat.jpg', 1500, '<h3>She passed MBBS in 2004 from Bangladesh Medical College under University of Dhaka. She did her FCPS in Internal Medicine from Bangladesh College of Physicians &amp; Surgeons (BCPS) in 2010. She worked in Bangladesh Medical College as an Assistant register for one year. Thereafter she joined in United Hospital Ltd as an Internal Medicine specialist from 2010 to 2014. She joined in Apollo Hospital as a specialist from 2014 to 2015.&nbsp;After that, in 2016 she joined&nbsp; United Hospital as a Junior Consultant and working as Associate Consultant.</h3>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:47:17'),
(43, NULL, 'Dr. Khan Md. Sayeduzzaman', 'MBBS,MCPS(Medicine), MD(Chest Diseases)', 'EID-14664\r\n', 'A-15952\r\n', 116, '2022100409461489223052_2_dr sayeduzzaman.jpg', 1500, '<p>Dr. Khan Md. Sayeduzzaman did his MBBS from Sher-E-Bangla Medical College in 1985; after that he attained post-graduation having MCPS in Medicine in 2002 and then he specialized in Respiratory Medicine and Chest Diseases with post-doctoral MD (Chest Disease) in 2006 from NIDCH (National Institute of Diseases of the Chest and Hospital).</p>\n\n<p>He has demonstrated expertise in managing problems of Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease e.g. chronic bronchitis &amp; emphysema like cough, shortness of breath, complications of smoking or air pollution. He also has long experience and proficiency in managing Airway Inflammatory Diseases &amp; Asthma, Respiratory Tract &amp; Lung Infections e.g. pneumonia.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>In his long three decades of career in government job, he served in NIDCH, Sir Salimullah Medical College &amp; Hospital (Mitford), Chittagong Medical College &amp; Hospital, Barisal SBMCH among others.</p>\n\n<p>Before joining United Hospital, he was serving as Associate Professor of Respiratory Medicine attached in Tang<a name=\"_GoBack\"></a>ail Medical College Hospital.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:46:37'),
(44, NULL, 'Dr. Ajmal Quader Chowdhury', 'MBBS, FCPS, MRCS', 'EID-14711 ', 'A-39068\r\n', 51, '2022100409441654431157_2_AJMAL QUADER CHOWDHURY (DR).jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS from Bangladesh Medical College under University of Dhaka in 2003</li>\n	<li>Completed FCPS in Surgery from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons (BCPS) in 2011</li>\n	<li>Completed MRCS in Surgery from Edinburgh, UK in 2012</li>\n	<li>Worked in Dhaka Medical College as a Registrar of Surgery from 2012 to 2016</li>\n	<li>Joined United Hospital on 2016 and currently serving as Associate Consultant in General Surgery Department</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-11-07 09:29:05'),
(45, NULL, 'Dr. Salina Akter', 'MBBS, MD', 'EID-14712\r\n', 'A-51439\r\n', 78, '2022100409431576067772_2_IMG_2367.jpg', 1500, '<h3>She passed MBBS in 2008 from Faridpur Medical College under University of Dhaka. She did her MD in Nephrology from Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University (BSMMU) in 2016. She worked in Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University (BSMMU) from 2011 to 2016. Thereafter she joined in United Hospital as a specialist from 2016 till now.</h3>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:43:26'),
(46, NULL, 'Dr. Arif Ahmed Mohiuddin', 'MBBS, MS (Cardiothoracic Surgery)', 'EID-14715\r\n', 'A-39898\r\n', 15, '2022100409401615697910_2_IMG_3452-6.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS degree from Sher-E-Bangla Medical College, Barishal under University of Dhaka in 2004.</li>\n	<li>Completed MS on Cardiothoracic Surgery (CTS) from National Heart Foundation Hospital &amp; Research Institute under University of Dhaka in 2016.</li>\n	<li>Joined Ministry of Health &amp; Family Planning, Govt of Bangladesh in 2005.</li>\n	<li>Worked in General Surgery department at Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University (BSMMU) and Sir Salimullah Medical College &amp; Mitford Hospital, Dhaka.</li>\n	<li>Served at National Institute of Cardiovascular Disease &amp; Hospital Dhaka (NICVD) as &nbsp;Assistant Registrar of Cardiac Surgery from 2015 to 2016.</li>\n	<li>Joined United Hospital in 2016 and at present serving as Junior Consultant in the department of Cardiac Surgery</li>\n	<li>Since 2016, serving in United Hospital Cardiac Surgery department, he is actively and successfully participating in coronary artery bypass grafting (CABG) surgery, aortic and mitral valve surgery (replacement and repair), Congenital Heart Surgeries like TOF, ASD, VSD and PDA repair surgeries on a regular basis.</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:40:25'),
(47, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Brig. Gen. Md. Abdul Mannan (Retd)', 'MBBS, MS (Ortho)', 'EID-14758\r\n', 'A-14955\r\n', 90, '2022100409401577169056_2_IMG_4692_edit.jpg', 1500, '<p>Obtained MBBS Degree from Barishal Sher-E-Bangla Medical Collage under University of Dhaka in 1984</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;Completed MS in Orthopaedics from NITOR under University of Dhaka in 2000</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;31 years&rsquo; experience in Orthopaedic department in deferent CMH Bangladesh Armed Forces</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;Long term departmental Head &amp; Advisor in Orthopedic in CMH Dhaka</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;Received General Surgery Training from Armed Forces Medical Institute (AFMI) , Dhaka in 1990</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;Received Fellowship in Arthroscopic &amp; Arthroplasty Surgery Knee from TURKEY</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;Completed Basic AO Trauma course in 2011</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;Received advanced training on Cadaveric Knee course from THAILAND in 2006</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;Joined in 2016 at Armed Forces Medical Collage Dhaka as Professor &amp; Head of the Department of Orthopaedics</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;Joined at United Hospital in 20016 as Consultant and now he is serving as a Senior Consultant in the department of</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Orthopedics</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp; Specialised in Orthopaedic Surgery in addition to all Fracture Fixation, Spine Fixation &amp; Discectomy, Specialty in Knee</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Arthroscopic, Reconstruction of ACL Meniscus, Total Knee Replacement &amp; Total Hip Replacement also&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:40:54'),
(48, NULL, 'Dr. Sultan  Mahmud\r\n', '', 'EID-15497\r\n', 'A-42022\r\n', 51, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(49, NULL, 'Dr. Soumen Chakraborty\r\n', '', 'EID-15681\r\n', 'A-43898\r\n', 16, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(50, NULL, 'Dr. Md. Helal Uddin', 'MBBS, D-Card, MSC', 'EID-15769\r\n', 'A-27282\r\n', 16, '2022100409341576145046_2_Dr. Md. Helal Uddin.jpg', 1500, '<p>He passed MBBS in 1997 from M.A.G Osmani Medical College, Sylhet. He did his MSC in Cardiology from Canterbury Christ Church University, UK in 2011. He completed his D-Card from National Institute of Cardiovascular Disease (NICVD), Dhaka in 2002. He also had training in Non-invasive Cardiology from Escort Heart Institute, India. He worked in Square Hospital as Specialist from 2007 to 2010. Thereafter he joined in United Hospital as a Junior Consultant in Cardiology Department from 2012 till now.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:34:51'),
(51, NULL, 'Dr. Mohammad Rafiur Rahman', 'MBBS, MS (CTS)', 'EID-15861\r\n', 'A38844\r\n', 15, '2022100409341639478377_2_1615697644_2_dr rafi.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS degree from Mymensingh Medical College under University of Dhaka in 2003</li>\n	<li>Completed MS in Cardio-Thoracic Surgery (CTS) from National Heart Foundation Hospital &amp; Research Institute (NHFH&amp;RI) under Dhaka University in 2014</li>\n	<li>Worked in National Heart Foundation Hospital &amp; Research Institute (NHFH&amp;RI), Mirpur, Dhaka at Cardiac Surgery Department as Surgical Resident from 2005 to 2014</li>\n	<li>After completing post-graduation degree he served as Junior Consultant in the departments of Cardiac Surgery in Chottogram Metropolitan Hospital, Dr. Sirajul Islam Medical College Hospital and Bangladesh Specialized Hospital from 2014 to 2018</li>\n	<li>Joined United Hospital in 2018 and at present serving as Junior Consultant in the department of Cardiac Surgery</li>\n	<li>In the United Hospital Cardiac Surgery department, he is actively and successfully participating to his full capacity in Bypass Grafting Surgery (CABG), Aortic and Mitral Valve Surgeries (Replacement and Repair), Congenital Heart Surgeries like ASD, VSD and PDA repair surgeries on a regular basis</li>\n	<li>He has attended several workshops abroad (Italy, India) related to Advanced Cardiac Surgery such as Valve Repair Surgery, Aortic Surgery and Heart Transplant and Mechanical Circulatory support Devices Surgery</li>\n	<li>Very much interested in Total Arterial Bypass Grafting Surgery, Aortic Surgery, Valve Repair Surgery, Minimal Invasive Cardiac Surgery (MICS), Heart Transplant and Various Short &amp; Long term Mechanical Circulatory Assist Devices Surgery</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:34:12'),
(52, NULL, 'Dr. S.M. Sadlee', 'MBBS,MRCP (UK)', 'EID-16015\r\n', 'A53671\r\n', 79, '2022100409311647866034_2_Dr. S. M. Sadlee.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:31:57'),
(53, NULL, 'Dr. Naima Siddiquee', 'MBBS, FCPS (Physical Medicine)', 'EID-16210\r\n', 'A-48195\r\n', 104, '2022100409311570362189_2_IMG_4552_edit.jpg', 1500, '<p>Dr. Naima Siddiquee passed MBBS in 2007 from Sir Salimullah Medical College under University of Dhaka. She has done her FCPS in PM&amp;R on 2014 from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons. She has had extensive hands-on training on PM&amp;R in DMCH &amp; BSMMU. She worked in various hospitals as physiatrist (PM&amp;R physician) and was in her own private practice before joining UHL.</p>\n\n<p>EDUCATION AND QUALIFICATIONS</p>\n\n<p>1. MBBS &ndash; Sir Salimullah Medical College, under University of Dhaka - 2007</p>\n\n<p>2. FCPS (Physical Medicine &amp; Rehabilitation)&ndash; Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons &ndash; 2014</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:31:36'),
(54, NULL, 'Dr. Md. Matiur Rahman', 'MBBS, MD(Card), FCPS', 'EID-16234\r\n', 'A-46186\r\n', 16, '2022100409301576146477_2_Dr. Md. Matiur Rahman.jpg', 1500, '<p>He passed MBBS in 2006 from Rangpur Medical College. He did his FCPS in Medicine from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons (BCPS) in 2015. He completed his MD in Cardiology from Dhaka Medical College in 2017. He worked in East West Medical College as Assistant Professor from 2017 to 2018. Before joining at United Hospital he worked in Ibn Sina Cardiac Centre as a Resident Consultant in 2018.</p>\n\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>OPD TIMING: 06:00 PM To 09:00 PM,&nbsp;DAYS: SUNDAY,&nbsp;TUESDAY&nbsp;&amp; THURSDAY</strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:30:07');
INSERT INTO `old_22_nov_22_doctors` (`id`, `doctor_id`, `doctor_name`, `degree`, `uhl_id`, `bmdc_id`, `dept_id`, `doctor_profile`, `doctor_fees`, `doctor_desc`, `doctor_edu`, `doctor_exp`, `status`, `is_deleted`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(55, NULL, 'Dr. Mohammad Arman Hossain', 'MBBS, MS (Cardiac Surgery)', 'EID-16253\r\n', 'A-34156\r\n', 15, '2022100409291660101221_2_Dr Arman.jpg', 1500, '<p>Obtained MBBS degree from Dhaka National Medical College, under University of Dhaka in 2001.<br />\n&bull; Completed MS from National Heart Foundation Hospital &amp; Research Institute under University of Dhaka in 2016.<br />\n&bull; Worked as Cardiac Surgery department at IBN Sina Specialized Hospital and Z.H. Sikder Women&rsquo;s Medical College and Hospital,&nbsp; National Heart Foundation Hospital &amp; Research Institute Dhaka.<br />\n&bull; Served as Registrar Surgery at Lab Aid Specialized Hospital, Dhanmondi&nbsp; and Dhaka National Medical College, Dhaka.<br />\n&bull; Took trainings on Cardiovascular and Thoracic Surgery from National Institute of Cardiovascular Disease(NICVD), National Heart Foundation(NHFH&amp;RI) and National Institute of Chest Hospital (NIDCH) .<br />\n&bull; Took trainings on General Surgery from SSMC &amp; Mitford hospital, Dhaka.<br />\n&bull; Also participate in Cardiovascular related training &amp; conference in Bangladesh &amp; abroad.<br />\n&bull; Very much interested in Total Arterial Bypass Grafting Surgery, Aortic Surgery, Valve Repair Surgery, Minimal Invasive Cardiac Surgery (MICS), Heart Transplant and Various Short &amp; Long term Mechanical Circulatory Assist Devices Surgery<br />\n&bull; Since 2018, serving in United Hospital Cardiac Surgery department, he is actively and successfully participating in coronary artery bypass grafting (CABG) surgery, aortic and mitral valve surgery (replacement and repair), Congenital Heart Surgeries like TOF, ASD, VSD and PDA repair surgeries on a regular basis.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:29:39'),
(56, NULL, 'Dr. Amina Sultana', 'MBBS, MD (critical care medicine)', 'EID-16391\r\n', 'A-34371\r\n', 61, '2022100409271654431051_2_Amina Sultana.jpg', 1500, '<p><br></p><p><br></p><p><strong>Skills and Training&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Training in Intensive Care Unit in BIRDEM ICU</li><li>Training in medicine department in Dhaka Medical College and Hospital</li><li>Training in respiratory medicine in National Institute of Diseases of Chest (NIDCH)</li><li>Training in Neuro Medicine in Dhaka Medical College</li><li>Training in Cardiovascular Medicine in National Institute of Cardiovascular Diseases (NICVD)</li><li>Training in medicine department in ShaheedSuhrawardy Medical College and Hospital</li><li>Internship training in Medical College for women and hospital</li><li>Specialized training Broncho’s Copy unit in NIDCH</li><li>Specialized training in casualty unit in DMCH</li><li>Specialized training in Burn Unit in DMCH</li><li>Specialized training in Renal Dialysis Unit, BIRDEM</li><li>Specialized training in Coronary Care Unit (CCU) NICVD</li><li>Specialized training in Postoperative Cardiac Surgery Unit in NICVD</li><li>Specialized training in Postoperative Neurosurgery Unit in Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical College University</li><li><strong>Certified in Advanced Cardiac Life Support (ACLS) according to American Heart Association (AHA)</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Research works:</strong></p><ul><li>RIFLE serum creatinine and urine output criteria combined is superior to RIFLE serum creatinine criterion alone in predicting Acute Kidney Injuru (AKI) in critically ill patients: A prospective observational study:BSSCM volume 8, number 1, March 2020</li></ul><p><strong>Special attention :</strong></p><ul><li>Proud student of first ever batch of MD in Critical Care Medicine in Bangladesh</li><li>Treasurer and EC member in Bangladesh Society of Critical Care Medicine</li><li>Participant in 15th&nbsp;Emirates Critical Care Conference as a speaker in 2019</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor of Medicine and Surgery (MBBS), Dhaka University (May 2000)</li><li>Doctor of Medicine (MD)-Critical Care Medicine,&nbsp;Dhaka University (January 2016)</li></ul><p><br></p>', '<p><strong>Twelve years work experience in country’s most well recognized ICUs</strong></p><ul><li>Worked as resident medical officer in BIRDEM ICU</li><li>Worked as senior house officer in United Hospital Limited</li><li>Worked as lecturer in Bio-Chemistry in Medical College for Women and Hospital</li><li>Worked as lecturer in Physiology in Medical College for Women and Hospital</li></ul><p><br></p>', 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-11-14 17:23:28'),
(57, NULL, 'Dr. Rawshan Arra Khanam', 'MBBS, MD (Chest Diseases)', 'EID-16561\r\n', 'A-38841\r\n', 116, '2022100409271563362363_2_Rwoshan Ara.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Completed her graduation (MBBS) from Shaheed Ziaur Rahman Medical College, Bogura under University of Rajshahi in 2003</li>\n	<li>Did her job &amp; post-graduation training in Internal &amp; Critical Care Medicine for six years from BIRDEM General Hospital, one of the largest, renowned, hospital in Bangladesh&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Obtained MD on Chest Diseases in 2013 from National Institute of Diseases of Chest &amp; Hospital (NIDCH), Dhaka</li>\n	<li>Worked in Delta Medical College &amp; Hospital as an Assistant Professor from 2013 to 2014</li>\n	<li>Worked at United Hospital in Medicine and later in Respiratory Medicine department as Junior Consultant from 2014 to 2018</li>\n	<li>Then she joined as Consultant at Ingenious Health Care Limited (Pulmonary Rehabilitation Centre) from 2018 to 2019</li>\n	<li>Her&nbsp; special field of interest is Interventional Pulmonology &amp; Noninvasive Ventilation (NIV). She has expertise in both diagnostic &amp; therapeutic&nbsp; Bronchoscopic procedures</li>\n	<li>She is also trained on sleep Medicine from Ace School of Sleep Medicine, New Dehli &amp; Singapore General Hospital</li>\n	<li>She attended many international seminars in Respiratory Medicine and presented scientific papers at home and abroad</li>\n	<li>She is the current Scientific secretary of Bangladesh Society of Critical Care Medicine (BSCCM) &amp; Executive Editor of Bangladesh Critical Care Journal (BCCJ)</li>\n	<li>She is a member of American College of Chest Physicians (ACCP)</li>\n	<li>She is also a Member of COVID Steering Committee of United Hospital</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:27:17'),
(58, NULL, 'Dr. Mirza Abul Kalam Mohiuddin', 'MBBS, MS (CTS)', 'EID-16603\r\n', 'A-18028\r\n', 15, '2022100409251633612887_2_Abul Kalam Mohiuddin_IMG_4421-2.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:25:56'),
(59, NULL, 'Dr. Shirin Akter\r\n', '', 'EID-16753\r\n', 'A-37348\r\n', 77, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(60, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. S. M. G. Kibria\r\n', '', 'EID-16948\r\n', 'A-14210\r\n', 51, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(61, NULL, 'Dr. Md. Ali  Zulkifl', 'MBBS, FCPS, FRCS', 'EID-17169\r\n', 'A-12884\r\n', 132, '2022100409241639573026_2_1593585577_2_drZulkifl.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS degree from Dhaka Medical College under University of Dhaka in 1983</li>\n	<li>Completed FCPS in Surgery from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons (BCPS) in 1990</li>\n	<li>Worked in National Health Service (NHS) of UK for four years during when he earned his FRCS from Royal College of Surgeons of England in 1993</li>\n	<li>Worked in Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University (BSMMU) from 1997 to 1999 where he was an active member of the Renal Transplantation Team</li>\n	<li>Worked at Square Hospitals as Consultant Urology and Urological Surgeon for seven years and also worked at Apollo Hospitals Dhaka (now Evercare Hospital) as Senior Consultant for three years</li>\n	<li>Received training in different disciplines of Renal Transplantation from Apollo Hospitals, Delhi on 2014</li>\n	<li>He has performed more than ten thousands of successful major urological surgeries. He is extremely experienced in managing of all kinds of stones of Urological system (e.g kidney stones, ureteric stones and bladder stones) through minimally invasive technique e.g. Laser URS, PCNL, RIRS</li>\n	<li>He is an expert in surgical management of kidney, prostate and bladder cancer and also an expert in management of female urological problems like frequency of urination and incontinence (lack of control to hold urine)</li>\n	<li>Before joining United Hospital as a Senior Consultant of Urology, he served in Asgar Ali Hospital as leading Consultant Urologist from 2016 till mid 2020</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:24:44'),
(62, NULL, 'Dr. Ashia  Ali', 'MBBS, FCPS', 'EID-17170\r\n', 'A-17645\r\n', 48, '2022100505271593605399_2_dr ashia.jpg', 1500, '<p>Dr. Ashia Ali did her graduation (MBBS) from Rangpur Medical College under University of Rajshahi in 1986. She did her Diploma in Anesthesia from University of Dhaka in 1998 and FCPS (Anesthesia) in 2003. She served in Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University in the department of Cardiothoracic Anesthesia for long 11 years from 2003 to 2014. Thereafter she joined Apollo Hospitals Dhaka (now Evercare Hospital) as Consultant Anesthesia &amp; ICU and served there from 2014 till 2016. Before joining United Hospital, she served Asgar Ali Hospital as Consultant of Anesthesia &amp; Pain Medicine from end 2016 till mid-2020.</p>\n\n<p>Dr Ashia is an expert in management of knee pain, back pain, shoulder pain, neck pain and post-operative long standing pain in addition to managing diabetes complications as in frozen shoulder, any cases of slip disc, severe myalgia and neuralgia. Managing cancer induced pain using Intrathecal pump to deliver morphine in spinal cord, is one of her special proficiency. She is a skilled practitioner of epidural injection, PRP (platelet rich plasma) therapy, ozone (O3) discectomy, dry needling, radio frequency ablation etc in minimizing different painful conditions.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-05 12:27:47'),
(63, NULL, 'Dr. Abu Mohammed Shafique', 'MBBS, MD (Cardiology)', 'EID-17197\r\n', 'A-22408\r\n', 16, '2022100509291639572469_2_1614502376_2_Shafique Sir_Final Image- 3Copy.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS degree from Sher-e-Bangla Medical College in 1992</li>\n	<li>Completed MD in Cardiology from Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University (BSMMU) (former IPGMR) in 2006</li>\n	<li>Received training in different disciplines of Cardiology from home and abroad</li>\n	<li>He has around 20 years&rsquo; experience in the field of Cardiology</li>\n	<li>Worked in United Hospital as Specialist Cardiologist in October 2006 to March 2008</li>\n	<li>Worked in Zia Heart Foundation Hospital as Chief Consultant from April 2008 to June 2010</li>\n	<li>Joined United Hospital on July, 2010 and worked as Consultant till November 2015</li>\n	<li>Worked in AFC Health Fortis Hospital, Chattogram as Chief Consultant and Cath-Lab Director from December 2015 to December 2018</li>\n	<li>Before re-joining United Hospital he worked in Metropolitan Heart Centre, Chattogram as Senior Consultant and Cath-Lab Director from 2019 till mid of 2020</li>\n	<li>He is skilled and expert in diagnosis &amp; management of all types of cardiac emergencies with invasive hemodynamic procedure, performing and reporting of Echocardiography, TMT, 24 hrs Holter Monitoring, Performing invasive procedure like coronary angiogram, PTCA, Primary PCI, PPM, TPM and other interventional procedures</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-05 16:29:16'),
(64, NULL, 'Dr. Nusrat  Jahan', 'MBBS, FCPS', 'EID-17431\r\n', 'A-40979\r\n', 64, '2022100505261576066978_2_Dr Nusrat.jpg', 1500, '<h3>She passed MBBS in 2004 from Dhaka Medical College &amp; Hospital under University of Dhaka. She did her FCPS in Internal Medicine from Bangladesh College of Physicians &amp; Surgeons (BCPS) in 2011. Before Joining at United Hospital she worked in Square Hospital from 2007 to 2008.</h3>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-05 12:26:18'),
(65, NULL, 'Dr. Mohammad Rabiul Karim Khan', 'MBBS, FCPS (Plastic & Reconstructive Surgery)', 'EID-17873\r\n', '34539\r\n', 106, '2022100505251612940962_2_Dr Rabiul Karim1.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>He obtained MBBS in 2001 from Rajshahi Medical College &amp; FCPS in 2013 from Bangladesh College of Physicians &amp; Surgeons, Dhaka, Bangladesh.</li>\n	<li>Dr. Mohammad Rabiul Karim Khan Papon Joined United Hospital on 7th&nbsp;February 2021 as a Consultant- Plastic &amp; Reconstructive Surgery, Department of Plastic Surgery.</li>\n	<li>He is currently working at Sheikh Hasina National Institute of Burn &amp; Plastic surgery, Dhaka as an Associate Professor.</li>\n	<li>He worked in different capacity at Dhaka Medical College Hospital such as, Assistant Registrar, Assistant Professor and Associate Professor.</li>\n	<li>He received Different training in the arena of Plastic &amp; Reconstructive Surgery and General Surgery from top plastic and cosmetic surgeons of Bangladesh and abroad.</li>\n	<li>His special interest are in general plastic surgery , pressure sore, cleft lip palate, hand surgery , vascular anomalies, skin cancer, diabetic foot, breast surgery, burn, cosmetic surgery etc.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>He has several publications and he participated in a number of conference at home and abroad.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-05 12:25:16'),
(66, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Md. Monwar  Hossain', 'MBBS, FCPS (ENT)', 'EID-17874\r\n', '12853\r\n', 38, '2022100409191612940739_2_dr monowar.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Prof. Monwar is a renowned Consultant who has more than 30 years of experience in the field of Otolaryngology and Head-Neck Surgery in Bangladesh.</li>\n	<li>He obtained MBBS in 1983 and passed FCPS(ENT) in 1992</li>\n	<li>He has advanced Training in Otology &amp; Head-Neck Surgery from USA, Singapore, Thailand &amp; India.</li>\n	<li>He has a total number of 25 Publication in different medical journal.</li>\n	<li>He was Ex-Principal as well as Professor in Mymensingh Medical College. He also served as Prof. in Sir Salimullah Medical College, Rajshahi Medical College, Shahid Ziaur Rahman Medical College (Bogra), National Institute of ENT&nbsp;Tejgaon, Dhaka.</li>\n	<li>Prior to joining United Hospital, he worked at BIRDEM General Hospital &amp; Ibrahim Medical College as Professor and Head of ENT starting from May, 2017 to December, 2020. He also worked as a part time Senior Consultant in Square Hospital Limited from 2006 to 2017</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:19:25'),
(67, NULL, 'Dr. Shahpar  Nahrir\r\n', '', 'EID-17888\r\n', '26226\r\n', 79, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(68, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Suraiya  Begum', 'MBBS, DCH, FCPS', 'EID-17997\r\n', '13082\r\n', 92, '2022100409141639477799_2_1622615470_2_Suraiya Begum Dr. Prof_IMG_3803_website.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Professor Dr. Suraiya Begum completed MBBS from Dhaka Medical College in 1983. Thereafter, she obtained DCH from IPGMR (BSMMU) in 1997 and obtained FCPS from BCPS, Dhaka in 2005</li>\n	<li>She received training on Pediatric Endocrinology from India in 2015</li>\n	<li>Her work experience includes serving in many renowned institutions in Dhaka including BIRDEM and Ibrahim Medical College, Shaheed Monsur Ali Medical College, Z.H. Sikdar Women`s Medical College and Shahabuddin Medical College</li>\n	<li>Professor Suraiya has numerous guided and co-guided researches, theses and publications</li>\n	<li>At present she is serving as Professor, Department of Pediatrics and Head of the unit, Pediatric Endocrinology, Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:14:19'),
(69, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. A.Q.M  Mohsen', 'MBBS, FCPS', 'EID-18156\r\n', '', 47, '2022100409121639478147_2_1621489918_2_A Q M Mohsen Sir.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:12:23'),
(70, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Quorrata Eynul Forhad\r\n', '', 'EID-18167\r\n', '23941\r\n', 85, NULL, 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-03 10:43:44'),
(71, NULL, 'Dr. Nazmul  Haque', 'FCPS (Paediatric Neurology & Development), FCPS (Paediatrics), MD (Paediatrics), BCS (Health), MBBS (DMC)', 'EID-18168\r\n', 'A-32735\r\n', 92, '2022100505221639477367_2_1623132288_2_Web Photo-Nazmul Haque_IMG_4863-1.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Completed MBBS from Dhaka Medical College in 2001</li>\n	<li>Completed FCPS in Paediatrics from BCPS in 2011 and did MD in Paediatrics from Dhaka Medical College in 2012 and he also completed FCPS in Paediatric Neurology &amp; Development from BCPS in 2019</li>\n	<li>Received two year Paediatric EEG training from department of Neuro Physiology of National institute of neurosciences and also completed one year EEG course from Kerala, India in 2020</li>\n	<li>Currently Serving as an Assistant Professor of Paediatric Neurology at National Institute of Neurosciences &amp; Hospital (NINS), Dhaka</li>\n	<li>Prior to joining at United Hospital, he worked at Popular Diagnostic Centre, Badda, Dhaka</li>\n	<li>He is life member of 7 International and National organizations of Pediatric Neurology and Epilepsy. He has several publications in National &amp; International Journal and also International journal reviewer at open journal of Paediatrics, USA</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-05 12:22:55'),
(72, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Muhammad Hafizur Rahman', 'MBBS, DEM (Diploma in Endocrinology & Metabolism), MD (Endocrinology & Metabolism)', 'EID-18173\r\n', 'A-24001\r\n', 36, '2022100409081622889966_2_Website_Hafizur Rahman_IMG_4682.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Prof. Dr. Muhammad Hafizur Rahman Obtained MBBS from Dhaka Medical College in 1984</li>\n	<li>He Completed DEM (Diploma in Endocrinology and Metabolism) from BIRDEM in 1990</li>\n	<li>He Obtained MD in Endocrinology and Metabolism from BIRDEM in 2006</li>\n	<li>He served various hospitals under Ministry of Health from 1985 to 2009. Then he joined Dhaka Medical College &amp; Hospital as Assistant Professor, Department of Endocrinology and later was promoted to Associate Professor and Professor where he served till December 2018</li>\n	<li>Prior to joining United Hospital he served at Popular Medical College Hospital as Consultant Endocrinologist</li>\n	<li>Professor Hafizur is currently appointed as General Secretary of&nbsp; Bangladesh Endocrine Society, Vice President of&nbsp; American Association of Clinical Endocrinologists (AACE), Bangladesh Chapter and Member of American Association of Clinical Endocrinologists (AACE)</li>\n	<li>He has several publications in national and international journal and participated in different national and international scientific seminars</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:08:12'),
(73, NULL, 'Dr. Asma  Siddique', 'MBBS, MPH(Nutrition), MCPS (Radiotherapy), F.C.P.S (Radiotherapy)', 'EID-18174\r\n', '', 86, '2022100409081639460210_2_1623490424_2_Dr. Asma IMG_4753.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:08:40'),
(74, NULL, 'Dr. Alim Akhtar Bhuiyan', 'MBBS, DTM&H (UK), MD (USA) Board Certified in Neurology (USA)', 'EID-18177\r\n', 'A-17824\r\n', 79, '2022100409061623132162_2_Web_Alim Akhter_IMG_4834.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Dr. Alim Akthar Bhuiyan is the only American Board Certified Neurologist and Epilepsy Specialist in the country. He graduated from Chattogram Medical College in 1988. Later, he obtained his Diploma in Tropical Medicine and Hygiene (DTM&amp;H) from London School of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene.</li>\n	<li>Dr. Bhuiyan has done post-graduate residency training in Internal Medicine from Queens Hospital Center (affiliated with Mount Sinai Hospital) under the City University of New York, USA</li>\n	<li>He did post-graduate residency training in Neurology &amp; Post-Doctoral Fellowship in Epilepsy and Clinical Neuro - Physiology from the State University of New York, Syracuse, USA. There, he was awarded&nbsp; Departmental Resident Teaching Award for Excellence in Medical Students&rsquo; teaching for two consecutive (1997 &amp; 1998) years</li>\n	<li>He obtained coveted Board Certification in Neurology from American Board of Psychiatry and Neurology</li>\n	<li>He has worked as a Consultant Neurologist at Veterans Administration (VA) Hospital in Syracuse, New York, USA</li>\n	<li>He was Associate Professor &amp; Head of the Department of Neurology at Bangladesh Medical College from 1999 to 2005</li>\n	<li>Prior to joining United Hospital as Full Time Senior Consultant, he was serving as Senior Consultant, Neurology in Evercare Hospital (former Apollo Hospitals Dhaka) since 2005</li>\n	<li>He has to his credit multiple national and international publications in Neurology</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:06:34'),
(75, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Md. Delwar  Hossain', 'MBBS, MD (Paediatrics)', 'EID-18218\r\n', '', 92, '2022100409051639459979_2_1625066547_2_Prof. Delwar_Paediatrics.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS from Chittagong Medical College in 1987</li>\n	<li>Completed MD in Paediatrics from BSMMU in 1998</li>\n	<li>Served in Government hospitals under Ministry of Health at different places from 1989 to 2003</li>\n	<li>Worked in Department of Paediatrics of National Institute of Kidney Disease &amp; Urology (NIDCU) as Assistant Professor, Associate Professor and Professor till May 2017</li>\n	<li>Joined Sylhet MAG Osmani Medical College as Professor of Department of Paediatrics and worked there till September 2018</li>\n	<li>Served Mymensingh Medical College as Professor &amp; Head, Department of Paediatrics from October 2018 till March 2021 prior to his joining at United Hospital as Senior Consultant Paediatrics</li>\n	<li>Has several publications in national and international journal, participated in different conference at home and abroad</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:05:25'),
(76, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Nilufar  Sultana', 'MBBS, FCPS (Obs & Gynae)', 'EID-18219\r\n', 'A14484\r\n', 85, '2022100409021639460100_2_1625066003_2_Prof. Nilufar Sultana.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Completed MBBS from Sylhet M A G Osmani Medical College in 1984. Thereafter, she obtained FCPS (ObGyn) from BCPS, Dhaka in 1998</li>\n	<li>Received training in Colposcopy, Laparoscopic surgery &amp; Fistula surgery and served as Master Trainer of fistula surgery in National Fistula Center at&nbsp; Dhaka Medical College Hospital; she has further received training in Reproductive Endocrinology &amp; Infertility from India and Sri Lanka; she was also involved in numerous research works</li>\n	<li>Served as a Professor and Head of the Department of ObGyn and Fertility Care Center (Reproductive Endocrinology &amp; Infertility) at Dhaka Medical College Hospital from 2013 to 2020</li>\n	<li>14 years of teaching experience at Dhaka Medical College for undergraduate and postgraduate course</li>\n	<li>Founder of 1st IVF centre in Government sector of the country in Dhaka Medical College Hospital</li>\n	<li>Worked in&nbsp; Evercare Hospital (previous Apollo Hospital) Dhaka as a Fixed Time Consultant for last six years prior to joining United Hospital</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:02:11'),
(77, NULL, 'Dr. Tangia  Muquith', 'MBBS, FCPS (Hematology) Clinical Fellow (Bone Marrow Transplant, NUH, Singapore)', 'EID-18307\r\n', 'A54412\r\n', 54, '2022100409021628078467_2_Tangia Muquith_IMG_6378_Web Photo.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS from Sir Salimullah Medical College &amp; Mitford Hospital, Dhaka in 2009</li>\n	<li>Enrolled in Post-graduation Training in Internal Medicine and Hematology from Dhaka Medical College Hospital and Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University</li>\n	<li>Achieved FCPS in Hematology from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons in 2016</li>\n	<li>She underwent a one year clinical fellowship programme on bone marrow transplant in National University Hospital, Singapore in 2019. She has experience of participating in more than 200 bone marrow transplant during her fellowship programme including both autologous and allogenic bone marrow transplant.</li>\n	<li>Prior to joining United Hospital as Junior Consultant of Hematology, she actively participated in more than 25 Bone Marrow Transplants in Hematology and Stem Cell Transplant Department of Evercare Hospital (previously Apollo Hospital)</li>\n	<li>She was awarded Young Siew Yoou Fellowship from NCIS, National University Hospital (NUH), Singapore in 2019</li>\n	<li>Her special area of interest is in vivo haploidentical bone marrow transplant for both benign hematological diseases and haematological malignancies.</li>\n	<li>She is also interested in treatment of lymphoproliferative disorder and related bone marrow transplant and immunotherapy</li>\n	<li>She attended various national and international seminars in hematology and bone marrow transplant and participated in observership training in Tata Medical Centre, Kolkata</li>\n	<li>She is a lifetime member of Bangladesh Society of Hematology</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 16:02:50'),
(78, NULL, 'Brig. Gen.(Retd.) Prof. Dr. Reza-ul Karim, SUP.', 'MBBS, MS (Ortho)', 'EID-18343\r\n', 'A 16602\r\n', 90, '2022100408581634377668_2_Rezaul Karim_IMG_7442.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS from Rangpur Medical College in 1986</li>\n	<li>Achieved MS in Orthopaedics from Dhaka University (NITOR) in 2002</li>\n	<li>Fellowship training in Spine Surgery at Phramongkutklao Army Hospital, Bangkok, Thailand in 2006</li>\n	<li>Completed Basic course in AO Spine at India in 2008, Advanced training in Spine Surgery at Singapore in 2012 and Advanced Training in Orthopaedic Surgery at Turkey in 2016</li>\n	<li>Served at different CMH&rsquo;s as Orthopaedic and Spine Surgeon from 2002 to 2015.</li>\n	<li>Dr. Reza-ul Karim was the Professor of Orthopaedics, Armed Forces Medical College, Dhaka from 2015 to 2017. He was chaired as Head of the Department and Adviser Specialist in Surgery (Orthopaedic) of CMH Dhaka from 2017 to October 2020</li>\n	<li>Prior to his joining at United Hospital as Senior Consultant, Orthopaedics; Professor Karim was the Chief Surgeon General at CMH Dhaka</li>\n	<li>Has several publications in different journals, participated many seminars, symposiums. Coordinated and supervised training of post graduate students</li>\n	<li>He can perform all kinds of major and minor fracture surgeries and experienced in management of multiple fracture on the day of admission. He is the pioneer in modern day spine surgery in Bangladesh Army. He is also very keen to do the different kind of joint replacement surgeries (even with mega prosthesis)</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 15:58:37'),
(79, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Chowdhury Md Ali', 'MBBS, DDV (DU)', 'EID-18378\r\n', 'A10800\r\n', 32, '2022100408571630498203_2_Mohammad Ali.jpg', 1500, '<p>More than 27 years of clinical experience in the field of Dermatology Venereology and Sexual Medicine</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS from Dhaka University in 1982</li>\n	<li>Achieved DDV from IPGM&amp;R, Dhaka University in 1993</li>\n	<li>Professor Chowdhury has 22 years of teaching experience in different medical colleges as registrar, Assistant Professor, Associate Professor and Professor. 8 years teaching experience at Dhaka Medical College for Undergraduate and Post Graduate students</li>\n	<li>Completed training on Sexual Medicine, Sexually Transmitted Diseases &amp; Male infertility from home and abroad</li>\n	<li>Dr. Mohammad Ali served several Government hospitals including Mymensingh Medical College Hospital, Sir Salimullah Medical College Hospital, Institute of Post Graduate Medicine and Reasearch, Shahid Ziaur Rahman Medical College, Shaheed Suhrawardy Medical College and Dhaka Medical College &amp; Hospital from 1982 to 2015</li>\n	<li>Prior to his joining at United Hospital as Senior Consultant, Dermatology; Professor Chowdhury worked at Dhaka Medical College &amp; Hospital as Professor and Head of the Dermatology Department</li>\n	<li>Has 26 publications in different prestigious journals. He is a member of the South Asian Society for Sexual Medicine (SASSM)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 15:57:57'),
(80, NULL, 'Dr. Syeda  Nur-E-Jannat', 'MBBS, FCPS (Internal Medicine), MD (Gastroenterology)', 'EID-18664\r\n', '37015\r\n', 47, '2022100408551635853192_2_Dr. Syeda Nur-E-Jannat.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 15:55:13'),
(81, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Shahrukh  Ahmed', 'MBBS, FCPS (Internal Medicine), MD (Neurology)', 'EID-18707\r\n', '11726\r\n', 79, '2022100408541635852934_2_Prof. Dr. Shahrukh Ahmed.jpg', 1500, '<p>&nbsp;Obtained MBBS from Dhaka Medical College in 1982</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp; Completed FCPS in Internal Medicine from BCPS in 1994</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp; Completed MD in Neurology from Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University (BSMMU) in 2004</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp; Did Post-Graduate Diploma in Clinical Research from Academy of Applied Pharmaceutical Sciences (AAPS), Toronto, Canada in</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2013</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp; Worked as Assistant Professor, Neurology in Sir Salimullah Medical College &amp; Mitford Hospital (SSMC&amp;MH) from 1995 to 2000</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp; Thereafter he worked at Mymensingh Medical College as Associate Professor and head of Neurology department from 2003 to</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2007 and later as Professor and Head of Neurology department from 2007 to 2011&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp; Prior to joining United Hospital as Full Time Senior Consultant, he was serving as Senior Consultant, Neurology in Labaid</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Specialized Hospital</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 15:54:45'),
(82, NULL, 'Mst. Hasina  Khatun', 'M.Phil in Clinical Psychology (DU), M.S in Clinical Psychology (DU), B.Sc in Psychology (DU)PGT in Psychotherapy (BSMMU)', 'EID-18711\r\n', '', 109, '2022100505191636898402_2_Hasina Khatun.jpg', 1500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-05 12:19:31'),
(83, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Md. Omar Ali', 'MBBS, FCPS (Surgery), WHO Fellowship in Laparoscopic & Endoscopic Surgery (Thailand)', 'EID-18741\r\n', '5820\r\n', 51, '2022100408491636897989_2_Omar Ali.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Passed MBBS from Rajshahi Medical College in 1976 with distinct result, Honors in anatomy, Physiology, Juris and Pathology; Stood first in 1st&nbsp;Professional examination, second in 2nd, 3rd&nbsp;and final Professional examination from Rajshahi University.</li>\n	<li>After Completion of 2 years residential training from Dhaka Medical College Hospital obtained FCPS degree from BCPS in Surgery in July 1982.</li>\n	<li>Served as Consultant in different district Sadar Hospital for 10 years and exercise experienced Surgical Skill for the vast majority of rural Population.</li>\n	<li>In 1991 entered in Medical teaching arena and since then served as Asst. Professor, Associate Professor and Professor on different Medical College like Dhaka Medical College, Rangpur Medical College, Barishal Sher-E-Bangla Medical College, Uttara Adhunik Medical College for about 30 years. During the long period of teaching life he has engaged in teaching and training of under Graduate and Post Graduate medical students.</li>\n	<li>He was regular examiner of under Graduate and Post Graduate examinations (FCPS, MS, MCPS). He was also PSC examiner for the recruitment of Medical teachers of different Surgical Specialty.</li>\n	<li>To cope with the Modern advancement of Surgical management he regularly enriched knowledge by attending different training program as basic surgical skill training of trainer in Johnson and Johnson training institute in Delhi; Laparoscopic Hernioplasty, Stapled Haemorrhoidectomy (Longo Operation) in Johnson&rsquo;s and Johnson&rsquo;s training institute in Bombay; WHO fellowship training in Laparoscopic Surgery in Siriraj Hospital, Bangkok, Thailand; training in National Institute of Medical Science, Sri Lanka.</li>\n	<li>He Also attended more than 50 International Seminar, Symposium and Workshop of different Country&rsquo;s as USA, Switzerland, Poland, Australia, China, India, Pakistan, Sri Lanka, Nepal, UAE, Saudi Arabia, Thailand, Philippine, Indonesia, Vietnam etc. Attended more than 100 Seminar, Symposium, Workshop and Conference in Bangladesh.</li>\n	<li>He had completed his thesis in management of hemorrhoids (Piles) as a Prerequisite of FCPS examination.</li>\n	<li>Having more than 25 publications on different scientific work.</li>\n	<li>Retired from Govt. Services on 2009 and Private medical college service on 2019 now working at Private Hospital.</li>\n	<li>During 40 years of Surgical experience he gained a lot of expertise and done enormous number of Surgeries including Laparoscopy (<strong>gall bladder, appendices, hernia), stomach, colon, rectum &amp; anal canal, intestine,&nbsp; hepatobiliary, pancreas, renal, endocrine, thyroid, breast, hydrocele, testis, lipoma, cyst, ulcers, gangrene, sinus, fistula, varicose vein,</strong>&nbsp;circumcision and many other general surgical procedures.</li>\n	<li>He also performs all abdominal emergencies including injury to the abdominal organs from road traffic and other accident, Perforation, Intestinal obstruction, Intra-abdominal abscess, Intra-abdominal hemorrhage, gastroIntestinal bleeding.</li>\n	<li>He has special interest in&nbsp;<strong>Intra-abdominal Cancer Surgery</strong>.</li>\n	<li>He has a good reputation as a renowned General and Laparoscopic Surgeon</li>\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-04 15:49:00'),
