(141, NULL, 'Dr. Kazi Ali Hassan', 'MBBS, M.Phil (EM), MRCP (UK)', 'HS01936\r\n', 'A-12869\r\n', 36, '2022100405411639478708_2_1580642347_2_dr kazi ali hasan.jpg', 1500, '<ul>\n	<li>Obtained MBBS degree from Mymensingh Medical College under University of Dhaka in 1983</li>\n	<li>Completed M.Phil in Clinical Endocrinology from BIRDEM in 1989</li>\n	<li>Obtained his MRCP degree in Internal Medicine from Royal College of Physicians of UK, in 2003</li>\n	<li>Obtained FRCP from Royal College of Physicians of Edinburgh in 2016</li>\n	<li>Worked as a Consultant Endocrinologist for 12 years in King Fahad Specialist Hospital, Saudi Arabia from 1993 to 2005 and gained vast experience in treating patients with diabetes, thyroid diseases and other hormonal disorders</li>\n	<li>Joined Bangladesh Medical College in 2005 as Assistant Professor of Endocrinology and in 2007 joined Square Hospitals Limited as a Consultant of Endocrinology and Internal Medicine</li>\n	<li>He is a highly experienced Endocrinologist with his collective working experience of more than 28 years in the field of Endocrinology at home and abroad</li>\n</ul>', ' <h4>Dhaka Medical College</h4>\r\n                                                            <p>MBBS, 1984</p>\r\n                                                            \r\n                                                            <h4> BIRDEM</h4>\r\n                                                            <p>DEM (Diploma in Endocrinology and Metabolism), 1990 </p>\r\n\r\n                                                            <h4> BIRDEM </h4>\r\n                                                            <p>MD in Endocrinology and Metabolism,2006 </p> ', ' <h4>Ministry of Health (1985-2009)</h4>\r\n                                                            <p>Assistant Professor, Department of Endocrinology</p>\r\n                                                            \r\n                                                            <h4> Dhaka Medical College & Hospital</h4>\r\n                                                            <p>Associate Professor, Department of Endocrinology</p>\r\n\r\n                                                            <h4> Dhaka Medical College & Hospital  </h4>\r\n                                                            <p>General Secretary </p> ', 1, 0, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-18 12:36:00'),
(142, NULL, 'Prof. Dr. Zeenat  Meraj sdf', 'MBBS, D.D (Bangkok), MCPS, FCPS', 'HS01944\r\n', 'A-14363\r\n', 32, '2022100404351582093096_2_Zeenat Meraj_IMG_7050-1.jpg', 1500, '<p>Dr. Zeenat Meraj passed MBBS from Dhaka Medical College &amp; Hospital (DMC) under University of Dhaka in 1982. She was awarded JICA scholarship and completed Diploma of Dermatology (DD) from Institute of Dermatology, Bangkok in 1997. She did her MCPS (Dermatology &amp; Venerology) in 2000 and FCPS (Dermatology &amp; Venerology) in 2005 from Bangladesh College of Physicians and Surgeons (BCPS), Dhaka. She did her FRCP from Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons, Glasgow in 2013. She also has trained in Aesthetic Dermatology, Lasers &amp; Hair Implant from Canada, Dubai, Singapore &amp; India. She served in different Institutions at home and abroad like Chittagong Medical College &amp; Hospital, Institute of Dermatology, Bangkok, Thailand, National University Hospital, Singapore. She also worked in BGCT Medical College, Chittagong as Professor &amp; Head of the Department from 2009 to 2011. She is the president of ADSB (Aesthetic Dermatology Society of Bangladesh), Board Member of SAARC AAD (South Asian Association of Regional Co-operation Association of Aesthetic Dermatology), Member of European Academy of Dermatology and Venereology, Member of American Academy of Dermatology, Life member of Bangladesh Dermatological Society. She attended lots of seminars and workshops at home and abroad. Before joined at United Hospital she worked in CSCR (Centre for Specialised care &amp; Research), Chattogram as Senior Consultant in the Department of Dermatology.</p>\n\n<p><strong>EDUCATION AND QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>MBBS &ndash; Dhaka Medical College &amp; Hospital (DMC) &nbsp;- 1982</li>\n	<li>Diploma of Dermatology (DD) - Institute of Dermatology, Bangkok &ndash; 1997</li>\n	<li>MCPS (Dermatology &amp; Venerology) &ndash; BCPS &ndash; 2000</li>\n	<li>FCPS (Dermatology &amp; Venerology) &ndash; BCPS &ndash; 2005</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>Experience</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Senior Consultant of CSCR (Centre for Specialised care &amp; Research), Chattogram from 2003 to 2020</li>\n	<li>Guest teacher of University of Science &amp; Technology Chittagong (USTC) from 2014 to 2017 and Expert Peer review committee of USTC from 2017 to present</li>\n	<li>Guest teacher of Ma O Shishu Medical college from 2011 to 2013</li>\n	<li>Professor &amp; Head of Department, Department of Dermatology, BGCT Medical College, Chittagong from 2010 to 2011</li>\n	<li>Associate Prof &amp; Head of Department, Department of Dermatology, BGCT Medical College, Chittagong from 2009 to 2010</li>\n	<li>Assistant Professor, Department of Dermatology, Chittagong Medical College &amp; Hospital from 2001 to 2009</li>\n	<li>Resident Physician, Department of Dermatology, Chittagong Medical College &amp; Hospital from 1999 to 2000</li>\n</ol>', '<p>xa</p>', '<p>adsadsa</p>', 0, 1, '2022-10-03 05:08:21', '2022-10-11 11:05:30'),
