(15, 'Newsletter-Issue-22,Quarter-2, 2018', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Our support to the community by offering Health Screening for prevention and detection of diseases saves one from the burden of disease load by early lifestyle changes &amp; treatment. Similarly we undertake aware- ness initiatives as reflected in National Nutrition Week where visitors got educated on differ- ent need-based diets; Hand Hygiene programs were also conducted in schools. Ortho- paedic Camp at Jamalpur and Paediatric Cardiology services to child patients with heart ailments, talk about our philan- thropic endeavors. Thought- provoking articles encompass- ing cases from varied clinical specialties make this edition interesting. Diploma course in Cardiac Nursing, adds a feather</span></p>', '2022111607061533643178cover22.jpg', 139, 1, 0, '2022-11-16 14:06:33', '2022-11-16 14:06:33'),
(16, 'Newsletter-Issue-21,Quarter-1, 2018', '<p>First edition of Newsletter in 2018 reflects some ground breaking endeavours like country’s first online pharmacy inauguration and philanthropic activities like free medical camp on Shadhinota Dibosh. Articles published are varied comprising cases of both adult &amp; child patients displaying a combination of acute and chronic conditions. Commemoration of several International Observance Days further added colours in the engaging activities in this quarter. Participation of hospital staff at different local &amp; international events continued as before, showing their efforts to be at par with current trends &amp; skills. Lastly the top-notch result of students of United College of Nursing portrayed our strengthened efforts ...</p><p><br></p>', '2022111607111525423396cover21.jpg', 6, 1, 0, '2022-11-16 14:11:56', '2022-11-16 14:11:56'),
